Show HN: App to help with planning, producing, reviewing, and publishing video
text:
Hey everyone, I've started working on an app to help companies, freelancers, and even individual content creators plan, produce, review, and publish their videos and streams in a more organised way. We're just getting started so not trying to sell anything at this point, but I do need feedback on where we're headed.

I recorded a video walkthrough of some mock-ups at https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mTtB_EkUA-M, or you can take a look at them yourself at https://www.synura.com/mockups/ (it is somewhat self-explanatory, but in the video I add more context). You can think of it as a potentially better, more organised alternative to having a bunch of stuff in random Google Docs and other places that you have to pass back and forth. I also eventually expect to add a lot of automatic post-processing type features (captioning, lighting/sound adjustments, "umm" removal, etc.) for people who don't know how to do that on their own.

Any kind of feedback at all is welcome, positive or negative, on whether there's an idea here that you think I could develop into something people would pay for, or if there's something you'd like to see in an app like this. Thanks in advance!

Ask HN: How do you use your (ultra/wide) monitor/s?
text:
Using a single ultra widescreen or multiple 16:9 or any other ratio monitors is now common even in office spaces must people are using at least two screens.

I wonder what is the setup for different HN readers. Being in software engineering or any other line of business. Some information that can probably be helpful for future searchers and readers:

- How many screens do you have? - What is aspect ratio of each screen? - What is your primary use of the setup?

As description please feel free to add your best practices, routines, etc. on how you maximise the usage.

text:

What I remember is that it made the example of a village as a system, and the max population the village could reach by foraging in a certain area. It was very long and there were lots of images illustrating the concepts. Searching systems thinking/theory on algolia didn't help. If you help me finding it back I would be very grateful.

text:
Please state the location and include REMOTE, INTERNS and/or VISA when that sort of candidate is welcome. When remote work is not an option, include ONSITE. Commenters: please don't reply to job posts to complain about something. It's off topic here.

Readers: please only email if you are personally interested in the job.
